etsysDvmrpExtMIB.name: etsysDvmrpExtMIB

revisions.description: The initial version of this MIB module

etsysDvmrpExtMIB.contactinfo: Postal: Enterasys Networks 50 Minuteman Rd. Andover, MA 01810-1008 USA Phone: +1 978 684 1000 E-mail: support@enterasys.com WWW: http://www.enterasys.com
etsysDvmrpExtMIB.description: This MIB module defines a portion of the SNMP MIB under the Enterasys Networks enterprise OID pertaining to the DVMRP configuration. This MIB was designed to be used in conjunction with the DVMRP-MIB [THALER1] for configuring the DVMRP parameters.

etsysDvmrpExtIfTable.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfTable
etsysDvmrpExtIfTable.description: This table provides addtional configuration objects that provide control for Enterasys DVMRP systems. This table augments the dvmrpInterfaceTable.

etsysDvmrpExtIfEntry.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfEntry
etsysDvmrpExtIfEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysDvmrpExtIfTable.

etsysDvmrpExtIfAdminStatus.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfAdminStatus
etsysDvmrpExtIfAdminStatus.description: The administrative state of DVMRP on this interface. When the status of this object is set to 'adminStatusDown', no DVMRP messages will be sent or received on this interface. The TIB state pertaining to this interface is cleared, resulting in the removal of the associated routes from the MFIB. When the status of this object is set to 'adminStatusUp', normal DVMRP operation will proceed, and multicast state is stored in the TIB when it is learned.

etsysDvmrpExtIfIfOperStatus.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfIfOperStatus
etsysDvmrpExtIfIfOperStatus.description: The current operational state of DVMRP on this interface.

etsysDvmrpExtIfStubInterface.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfStubInterface
etsysDvmrpExtIfStubInterface.description: Indicates whether this interface is a stub interface in relation to DVMRP. If this object is set to 'true', no DVMRP packets are sent out this interface, and any received DVMRP packets are ignored. Setting this object to 'true' is a security measure for interfaces towards untrusted hosts. To communicate with other DVMRP routers using this interface, this object must remain set to 'false'. Changing the value of this object while the interface is operationally active MAY cause the interface to be deactivated and then reactivated.

etsysDvmrpExtIfP2PNoHellos.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfP2PNoHellos
etsysDvmrpExtIfP2PNoHellos.description: Indicates whether this interface is a point-to-point interface. If the value of this object is 'true', neighbors are not required to send DVMRP-Hello messages. This is provided for backward-compatibility with some older implementations that do not send DVMRP-Hellos on point-to-point links. Changing the value of this object while the interface is operationally active MAY cause the interface to be deactivated and then reactivated.

etsysDvmrpExtIfHelloInterval.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfHelloInterval
etsysDvmrpExtIfHelloInterval.description: The transmit frequency of DVMRP Hello messages on this interface. A value of 0 represents an infinite interval and periodic DVMRP Hello messages SHOULD not be sent on this interface.

etsysDvmrpExtIfHelloHoldtime.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfHelloHoldtime
etsysDvmrpExtIfHelloHoldtime.description: The amount of time a DVMRP neighbor should consider this router operationally up.

etsysDvmrpExtIfReportInterval.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfReportInterval
etsysDvmrpExtIfReportInterval.description: The transmit frequency of DVMRP Report messages on this interface. A value of 0 represents an infinite interval and periodic DVMRP Report messages SHOULD not be sent on this interface.

etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrTable.name: etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrTable
etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrTable.description: This table provides objects that manipulate the operation of the DVMRP Tree Information Base (TIB) Manager in order control the acceptable limits for the TIB.

etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrEntry.name: etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrEntry
etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrTable.

etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrKeepalivePeriod.name: etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrKeepalivePeriod
etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrKeepalivePeriod.description: The amount of time to keep (S,G) state alive in the absence of DVMRP (S,G) Join messages or (S,G) data packets. Note: Configuring different values for this object for different routers in the DVRMP domain may lead to incorrect protocol operation.

etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrMetric.name: etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrMetric
etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrMetric.description: A global distance metric that is used to calculate distance vectors. An interface SHOULD inherit this value if its default metric (dvmrpInterfaceMetric) has not been modified.

etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrSGStateLimit.name: etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrSGStateLimit
etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrSGStateLimit.description: The maximum number of {source, group} pairs for which the DVMRP TIB Manager is allowed to store non-interface specific (S,G) state. A value of zero means that there is no limit.

etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrSGStateWarnThold.name: etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrSGStateWarnThold
etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrSGStateWarnThold.description: The DVMRP TIB Manager logs an exception if the number of {source, group} pairs for which it is storing non-interface specific (S,G) state exceeds this value. A value of zero means that there is no warning threshold.

etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrSGStateStored.name: etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrSGStateStored
etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrSGStateStored.description: The number of {source, group} pairs for which the DVMRP TIB Manager is storing non-interface specific (S,G) state.

etsysDvmrpExtIfGroup.name: etsysDvmrpExtIfGroup
etsysDvmrpExtIfGroup.description: This group defines interface controls for Enterasys DVMRP systems.

etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrGroup.name: etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrGroup
etsysDvmrpExtTibMgrGroup.description: This group defines the Tree Information Base (TIB) manager objects for Enterasys DVMRP systems.

etsysDvmrpExtCompliance.name: etsysDvmrpExtCompliance
etsysDvmrpExtCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that support etsysDvmrpExt.
